headline.main: EUROPEAN AFFAIRS.; The News in England--Comments of the London Press. THE WRECK OF THE ARCTIC. EXTRACTS FROM OUR FOREIGN FILES. ARRIVAL OF THE NIAGARA'S MAILS.

docs.lead_paragraph: We have had enough of late, and more than enough, of the calamities of war. Our readers must have been surfeited with the appalling intelligence received from the East of deaths incurred upon the field of battle, and of the still more awful condition of those who were struck down, maimed, or wounded, to implore in vain the succor which had not been provided in time.

headline.main: NEW-YORK CITY.; The House of Refuge. Return of the Egyptian Commissioners. Irishmen's Union. Sweeping Broadway--A Suggestion. Catholic Jubilee--Catholic Pastoral of Archbishop Hughes. Barnum's Menagerie Breaking Up--The Horses Sold. Burnam's Autobiography--The Question settled. Western Farm League. THE DEAF AND DUMB. COMMON COUNCIL PROCEEDINGS. Inebriate Asylum- Naturalization. A Prisoner Rescued. Professor Adler. Aldermen Releasing Prisoners. Stabbing in Broadway. A Primary School Disturbed. Smuggling.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Semi-Annual Examination at the House of Refuge took place in the Chapel of the House last Wednesday afternoon, commencing at 4 o'clock. The boys some 307 in number, were pat through their various exercise: the order classes passing very creditable examination. Better order than was preserved, from the beginning to the close, would not be desirable.

docs.lead_paragraph: His Honor, Judge GRAY, left Binghamton a little earlier than Judges usually do when they come to hold a Circuit Court in this village, and one hundred cases are marked down for trial on the calender. His Honor left without disposing of a single cause. His Honor came here in good humor, but be lost nothing, since he left in bad humor.

headline.main: Horrible Tragedy in Orange County--Murder and Suicide.

docs.lead_paragraph: A shecking affair, by which a man and wife nemed SMITH were sent into etersity, occurred in the village of New-Windsor, about four miles from Newburg, on Saturday night last. The husband has been for some times in depressed state of mind, and finally wound up his earthly career by murdering his wife and then taking his own life.
